to the editor akhil reed amar op ed nov 9 argues that the electoral college is unfair to racial minorities but political scientists have argued that it gives blacks and hispanics a little more influence in selecting the president because they tend to live in the large cities of the bigger states which encourages candidates of both parties to appeal for their votes so the electoral college does in fact play an important role in helping minorities achieve racial justice ronald d rotunda washington nov 9 2000 the writer is a visiting senior fellow in constitutional studies at the cato institute

